President Joe Biden met with NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg to discuss the upcoming NATO Summit in Vilnius. They focused on the implications of Russia's war on Ukraine for transatlantic security and the need to strengthen NATO's deterrence and defense. They also discussed the support provided by Allies and partners to Ukraine in defending itself against Russian aggression. The leaders emphasized the importance of fulfilling the defense investment pledge made at the 2014 Wales Summit. Additionally, they expressed their shared desire to welcome Sweden to the Alliance soon. President Biden expressed his anticipation for hosting the NATO Allies in Washington, D.C. for NATO's 75th anniversary summit in July 2024.